verbs.description: upsolve (third-person singular simple present upsolves, present participle upsolving, simple past and past participle upsolved)

examples: They were both broiled o' th' coles i and a man may smell broil'd meat, I hope ? you are a scholar, upsolve me that, now.

entries.meaning: (competitive programming, neologism) To solve a problem after the end of a contest.
